modules.description: The library offers numerical optimization algorithms spanning global and local search strategies, including gradient-based, derivative-free, and constrained methods. It operates on float arrays to define parameters and constraints, supporting use cases like bound-constrained optimization, nonlinear constraint handling, and convergence control through tolerances or evaluation limits. Key algorithms such as MMA, COBYLA, and Nelder-Mead enable solving problems requiring precise gradient exploitation or derivative-free exploration under complex constraints.
